- "validated" refers to datasets that have passed a quality check and are considered reliable;
- "user activities" include views and downloads, which indicate the engagement of users with the datasets;
- "location" refers to the geographical area from which the data was collected.

- "Years of life lost (YLLs)" is a measure of premature mortality, representing the sum of the differences between a standard life expectancy and the ages at which individuals died.;
- "Validated sources" are those data sources that have been reviewed and confirmed to meet certain quality standards.;
- "Government sources" are data sources provided by government agencies, which are typically considered reliable and authoritative.

sql:
SELECT age_range, average_life_expectancy 
FROM ages 
ORDER BY average_life_expectancy DESC;

SELECT average_life_expectancy, age_range, age_group_description
FROM ages
ORDER BY average_life_expectancy DESC;
